agents

Enum Flags

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Flags>
      • agents.Flags
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Flags>

    public enum Flags
extends java.lang.Enum<Flags>
    A flaggable enumeration example for Java where the Message flags are specified using bit-shifted values and stored in the message via an integer. Behaviour in this class is similar to how the System.Flags attribute works on enumeration types in C# as well as the implementation of their HasFlag() extension method.
